non-relativistic speeds characteristic plasma velocities, in particular, the constant sound speed a  are very small compared to the speed of light, the constant  is a very small but fixed parameter. In this paper, unlike the classical statement in [2, 4, 18, 14, 15], we do not set  = 0 in (15b) and consider the full Maxwell equations in vacuum. We show that in spite of the fact that  is a very small constant a large enough vacuum electric field crucially influence on the stability of a non-relativistic plasma-vacuum interface. Thus, in our new statement the non-relativistic plasma is still described by the MHD equations (3)2 whereas the vacuum magnetic and electric fields obey the Maxwell equations (15). As in [19], for technical simplicity we consider the case of unbounded domains. Namely, we assume that the domains  (t) = {x1  (t, x )} represent the plasma and vacuum regions respectively. On the interface (t) = {F (t, x) = x1 - (t, x ) = 0} we still have the boundary conditions (8), where the jump [q ] is given by (13) and q is the total
