5.8

Numerical investigation

It should be noted that condition (75) is only sufficient for instability for the particular case (72) because normal modes analysis was performed under the restriction 3 = 0 on the wave vector. For finding a necessary and sufficient instability condition we have to repeat our above analysis for an arbitrary wave vector  (with | | = 1). Since it is technically impossible to do this analytically, we do numerical calculations by using MATLAB software. Just for technical simplicity we consider the static case v ^3 = 0. Repeating the arguments above, we obtain the following counterparts of (105) and the Lopatinski determinant (113) for the general case of the wave vector  = (2 , 3 ) = (cos , sin  ): p = - 1 + 4
