We fix	= 10-6 and four different values of H 3 : H 3 = 1, H 3 = 2/3, H 3 = 0.5 and H 3 = 0.25. Then, we choose the partition of the interval (0, 2 ) with the step 10-2 for the angle	and for all its points numerically solve equation (114) for  . The results of these calculations in the plane of parameters E1 and H2 are presented in Fig. 1, where the union of domain 1 and 4 is the whole instability domain for case (72) with v ^3 = 0. Recall that domain 1 is the domain described by the sufficient instability condition (75) found analytically.

